Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, low urine specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal impairment. Low total CO₂ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (glucose, ketones, protein) and low HbA1c are unusual together; consider possible acute kidney injury with impaired filtration. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended. No evidence of urinary tract infection.
